{
  "texts": [
    "S4 struggles more than LSTM with bond assignment, and generates remarkably fewer errors than both benchmarks in branching and ring design.",
    "Our hypothesis is that bond assignment indicates good learning of \"short-range\" dependencies, while branching and ring opening and closure require better capturing of the \"long-range\" relationships.",
    "This suggests that S4 captures relatively \"long-distance\" relationships well, in agreement with existing evidence in other domains [33] [34] [35].",
    "Capturing bioactivity.",
    "We evaluated S4 for its ability to learn elements of bioactivity."
  ]
}